Title: FSSAI License/Registration Related Queries
Description: Food Safety Connect helps consumers to register their complaints and feedbacks about food safety issues related to adulterated food, unsafe food, substandard food, labelling defects in food and misleading claims & advertisements related to various food products. On successful registration of a food concern, Consumer receives a unique concern no. via SMS on the mobile number provided at the time of registering the concern. This reference no. can be used at a later time to track his/her concern in the online system. The FSSAI team, the State DOs/FSOs and the FBOs – all three stakeholders have online access to the grievances raised by consumers.

Title: Telangana: Department of Road Transport Authority- Surrender Of Permit

Description: The Department of Agriculture, Puducherry with an intention of tiding over the scarcity of Sugarcane setts for the sugarcane growers at the time of planting and to promote sugarcane cultivation extends back ended subsidy to farmers who raise sugarcane nurseries and distribute the setts to the registered cane growers of the command area. The beneficiary has to submit the application at the Farm Help Centres or the headquarters of the extension wing; online submission would be facilitated and subsidy is extended subject to the satisfaction of the guidelines in force.

Title: Back ended subsidy for Natural Calamities, Puducherry
Description: The Department of Agriculture, Puducherry extends back end assistance to farmer / farm women in case of occurence of any Natural Calamities such as drought / heavy rains and notified by the Government. The Farmer/ Farm women who wish to avail the assistance has to submit an application form along with the Smart Farmer Identity Card at the Farm Help Centres; Online submission would be facilitated; fields inspected and then the assistance is allowed subject to the satisfaction of the guidelines in force.

Title: Back ended subsidy for Submersible Motors, Puducherry
Description: The Department of Agriculture, Puducherry extends subsidy for Micro Irrigation such as Submersible Motors with an aim to optimize the utilisation of water for farming and ultimately saving the depletion of ground water. The beneficiary has to submit an application at the State Ground Water Unit; online submission would be facilitated and the subsidy is extended subject to the satisfaction of the guidelines in force.

Title: Back ended subsidy for Tubewell Construction, Puducherry
Description: The Department of Agriculture, Puducherry extends subsidy for Micro Irrigation such as Tubewell Construction with an aim to optimize the utilisation of water for farming and ultimately saving the depletion of ground water. The beneficiary has to submit an application at the State Ground Water Unit; online submission would be facilitated and the subsidy is extended subject to the satisfaction of the guidelines in force.

Title: Back ended subsidy for Pipelining, Puducherry
Description: The Department of Agriculture, Puducherry extends subsidy for Micro Irrigation such as Pipelining with an aim to optimize the utilisation of water for farming and ultimately saving the depletion of ground water. The beneficiary has to submit an application at the State Ground Water Unit; online submission would be facilitated and the subsidy is extended subject to the satisfaction of the guidelines in force.

Title: Back ended subsidy for Drip Irrigation, Puducherry

The beneficiary has to submit an application at the State Ground Water Unit; online submission would be facilitated and the subsidy is extended subject to the satisfaction of the guidelines in force.

Title: Back ended subsidy for Sprinkler Irrigation, Puducherry
Description: The Department of Agriculture, Puducherry extends subsidy for Micro Irrigation such as Sprinkler Irrigation with an aim to optimize the utilisation of water for farming and ultimately saving the depletion of ground water. The beneficiary has to submit an application at the State Ground Water Unit; online submission would be facilitated and subsidy is extended subject to the satisfaction of the guidelines in force.

Title: Back Ended Subsidy for Farm Machinery / Agricultural Implements, Puducherry
Description: The Department of Agriculture, Puducherry extends subsidy for Farm Machinery / Agricultural Implements to facilitate mechanisation of farm operations. The beneficiary has to submit an application at the Government Agricultural Engineering Workshop; online submission would be facilitated and subsidy extended for Farm Machinery like Tractor, Power Tiller etc., Improved Agricultural Implements and Conventional Agricultural Implements subject to the satisfaction of the guidelines in force.

Title: Back ended subsidy for Certified Seed Production, Puducherry
Description: The Department of Agriculture, Puducherry extends subsidy for the production of certified seeds so that an increased production of certified seeds would lead to wider usage of good quality seeds thereby reducing the incidence of pests and diseases and also increase the production. The beneficiary has to submit an application along with the Smart Farmer Identity Card; Online submission would be facilitated; and subsidy allowed subject to the satisfaction of guidelines in force.

Title: Back ended subsidy for Horticulture, Puducherry
Description: The Department of Agriculture, Puducherry extends back ended subsidy for Horticultural crops to encourage the horticultural farmers as well as to support their cost of cultivation. To avail the subsidy, the farmers / farm women in posession of Smart Farmer Identity Card has to submit an application at the Horticultural wing of the Department of Agriculture, Puducherry; online submission would be facilitated; field inspected and then subsidy allowed after harvest subject to satisfaction of guidelines in force.

Title: Back ended subsidy for Paddy, Puducherry
Description: The Department of Agriculture, Puducherry extends back ended subsidy for paddy cultivation to encourage the paddy farmers as well as to support their cost of cultivation. To avail the subsidy, the farmers / farm women in posession of Smart Farmer Identity Card has to submit an application at the Farm Help Centres of the Department of Agriculture, Puducherry; online submission would be facilitated; field inspected and then subsidy allowed after harvest subject to satisfaction of guidelines in force.

Title: Issue of Agricultural Inputs Permits, Puducherry
Description: The Department of Agriculture, Puducherry extends subsidy on Agricultural Inputs to eligible Farmers / Farm Women to support their farming. The Farmer / Farm Women has to submit the Smart Farmer Identity Card issued by the Department at the farm Help Centers and on authentication, permits for the agricultural inputs required for the season would be issued by the Farm Help Centres. The Input permit is to be produced at the Agro Department assiged to avail the subsidized agricultural inputs.

Title: Issue of Smart Farmer Identity Card, Puducherry
Description: The Department of Agriculture, Puducherry issues Smart Farmer Identity Card to eligible Farmers/Farm Women to avail subsidy / assistance for farming. On submission of applications, Smart Farmer ID Cards are issued to Farmers / Farm Women subject to the satisfaction of the documents produced - Land ownership document; Lease deed; FMB; Chitta; Adangal; Site Map; Aadhar of applicant & nominee; EPIC of applicant & nominee; PP size Photo etc., The forms could be obtained from the Farm Help Centres and online submission would be facilitated. Before online submission the document would be verified and field inspected, if needed.

Title: Online Application for Issue of Prosthetic appliance to the Differently Abled Persons, Puducherry
Description: Prosthetic appliances like calipers, Tricycles, Crutches, hearing aid spectacles / low vision aids, etc. on the advice of the specialists concerned attached to the Govt. General Hospital Pondicherry /Karaikal / Mahe / Yanam are given to the Differently abled persons (with 40% and above disability and annual income not exceeding ₹75,000/-).

Title: Online Application for Incentive to Eye Donors, Puducherry
Description: A cash incentive of ₹10,000/-  is given to the nearer relation of the Eye Donors.

Title: Online Application for Fresh Scholarship for the Physically Handicapped students, Puducherry
Description: Deserving Differently Abled Students (with 40% and above disability and annual income not exceeding ₹ 75,000/-) are awarded with Scholarship through their respective schools. Applications are called for during July/August of every Academic year. For I–V Std. ₹1000/- p.a., for VI–VIII Std. ₹2000/- p.a., for IX–XII Std. ₹3400/- p.a., for U.G. Courses ₹5000/- p.a., and for P.G / Professional courses ₹6800/- p.a.

Title: Online Application for Marriage Incentive/Assistance to PH and Normal and both Differently Abled Persons, Puducherry
Description: For marriage between Differently abled persons: Marriage Incentive of ₹50,000/- is given for marriage between Differently abled persons (with 40% and above disability and annual income not exceeding ₹75,000/-). A sum of ₹20,000/- is paid in cash one time and ₹30,000/- in the form of NSC Bonds.

Title: Online Application for Issue of Motorized Tricycle to Ortho Handicapped persons, Puducherry
Description: Invalid Carriages (Motorized Tri-Cycles) to severely ortho Differently Abled Persons are provided so that they can be mobile. Applicant should have an ortho disability of more than 65% and annual income not exceeding ₹75,000/-.

Title: Online Application for Obtaining ID Card for Differently abled persons, Puducherry
Description: An identity card is being issued to all the Differently Abled Persons (with 40% and above disability and annual income not exceeding ₹75,000/-) indicating their personal details for ready reference to avail the benefits of welfare scheme.

Title: Online Application for Funeral expenses to Physically Handicapped persons, Puducherry
Description: Funeral expenses of the deceased Differntly Abled person (with 40% and above disability and annual income not exceeding ₹75,000/-) is provided by giving a sum of ₹5,000/- to the immediate relation of the dead person.

Title: Online Application for Fuel Subsidy to Physically Handicapped persons, Puducherry
Description: A Fuel Subsidy of 50% of fuel cost is given, subject to a maximum of 25 Litres, to the Differently abled persons (with 40% and above disability and annual income not exceeding ₹75,000/-).

Title: Online Application for Transport allowance to Physically Handicapped persons, Puducherry
Description: Differently abled persons (with 40% and above disability and annual income not exceeding ₹75,000/-) are provided with a transport allowance of ₹100/- monthly and the payment will be made through their respective Anganvadis.

Title: Online Application for Financial Assistance to Differently Abled Persons, Puducherry
Description: Financial assistance to the differntially abled persons, whose annual income does not exceed Rs.75,000/-, are provided, monthly, in three ranges, according to the “percentage (degree) of disability”, viz., (i) 40-65% (₹1,500/- p.m.); (ii) 66-85%- (₹2,000/- p.m.); and (iii) 86-100% (₹3,000/- p.m.), through their respective Anganvadis.

Title: Application for Renewal of Business Licenses under section 330
Description:
" Factory, etc. not to be established without permission of Commissioner.

1) No person shall, without the previous permission in writing of the Commissioner, establish in any premises, or materially alter, enlarge or extend , any factory, workshop or trade premises, in which it is intended to employ steam, electricity, water or other mechanical power.

2) The Commissioner may refuse to give such permission, if he is of the opinion that the establishment, alteration, enlargement or extension of such factory, workshop or trade premises, in the proposed position would be objectionable by reason of the density of the population in the neighborhood thereof, or would be a nuisance to the inhabitants of the neighborhood"

Description:
"A Licence, under section 128 of the Haryana Municipal Act,1973, for premises to be used for any of the purpose mentioned in sub-section (1) of that section may be granted by the committee, on the application of the owner or occupier of such premises, and shall be issued by an officer, appointed by the committee, in form A appended to these bye-laws on payment of fees specified in the schedule to these bye-laws and in other case as may be approved by Deputy Commissioner under sub-section(3) of section 128 and on the conditions detailed by bye-laws 6 :

Provided that license fee for each such trade or different types of business carried on in one place and listed in the serial number in the schedule to these bye-laws shall require separate license for cash serial number excepting those serial numbers in which it is indicated otherwise."

Title: Haryana : Application for Revision of Fire NOC
Description: As per Haryana Fire Service Act, 2009, any person proposing to construct a building to be used for any purpose other than residential purpose or a building proposed to be used for residential purpose of more than 15 meters in height, such as group housing, multi-storeyed flats, walk up apartments, etc. before the commencement of the construction, shall apply for the approval of Fire Fighting Scheme conforming to national Building Code of India, the Disaster Management Act, 2005 (53 of 2005), the Factories Act, 1948 (Act 63 of 1948) and the Punjab Factory Rules, 1952, and issue of no objection certificate on such form, alongwith such fee, as may be prescribed.

Title: Haryana : Sanction of Sewerage Connection in Cities and MC Towns

The consumer can  check the status of the application online and take the  online print  of sanction letter.

Title: Jansuraksha
Description:
For creating a Universal Social Security system, especially for poor and under privileged the following schemes are available:
  1. Pradhan Mantri Jeevan Jyoti Bima Yojana(PMJJBY):-
PMJJBY is life insurance scheme for persons on the age group of 18 to 50 years having a saving bank account. This scheme offers a renewable insurance coverage of Rs. 2 Lakh at a premium of Rs. 330 per annum.     ;
2. Pradhan Mantri Suraksha Bima Yojana(PMSBY):-
PMSBY is accident insurance scheme for persons in the age group of 18 to 70 years having a saving bank account. The risk coverage under the scheme is Rs. 2 Lakh for accidental death and full disability and Rs. 1 Lakh for partial disability at a premium of Rs. 12 per annum.       ;
3. Atal Pension Yojana(APY):-
APY is pension scheme for all persons in the age of 18 to 40 years having saving bank account in bank/post offices. Subscribers will receive guaranteed monthly pension at the age of 60 years, based on defined contribution. The scheme is administered by the Pension Fund Regulatory and Development Authority(PFRDA) under the overall administrative and institutional architecture of the National Pension System[NPS]

Title: Give It Up - voluntarily surrender  LPG subsidy
Description: Domestic LPG is heavily subsidized by the Government of India and every cylinder that we use in our kitchen carries a substantial subsidy. This translates to a huge annual subsidy burden on the Government, draining precious resources which otherwise could have been used in developmental activities. Subsidy on domestic LPG instead of being universal needs to meet the needs of the truly needy citizens. Fortunately, many able and aware citizens are not in favor of subsidies and would rather pay the full price for the products and, thereby they also make a personal contribution towards nation-building. There is a need to spread this message. Accordingly, the Government has launched the ‘#GiveItUp’ campaign which is aimed at motivating LPG users who can afford to pay the market price for LPG to voluntarily surrender their LPG subsidy.

Title: Application form for Pradhan Mantri Ujjwala Yojana (PMUY)
Description:
PMUY aims to safeguard the health of women & children by providing them with a clean cooking fuel – LPG, so that they don’t have to compromise their health in smoky kitchens or wander in unsafe areas collecting firewood.
PMUY was launched by Hon’ble Prime Minister Shri Narendra Modi on May 1st, 2016 in Ballia, Uttar Pradesh. Under this scheme, 5 Cr LPG connections will be provided to BPL families with a support of Rs.1600 per connection in the next 3 years. 
Ensuring women’s empowerment, especially in rural India, the connections will be issued in the name of women of the households. Rs. 8000 Cr. has been allocated towards the implementation of the scheme. Identification of the BPL families will be done through Socio Economic Caste Census Data.

Title: Online submission of proposal to DBT
Description: This user friendly system is created to facilitate online submission of proposal and various other documents related to ongoing projects to the Department of Biotechnology. You can read proposal submission guidelines, reviewer guidelines, taskforce guidelines, etc.

Title: Apply and search student scholarships online
Description: Students can register online on the Vidya Lakshmi Portal to search and apply for educational scholarships. You can register, fill up a single form and apply to multiple banks for educational loans. Users can also find information on registered banks, loan schemes, students registered, loans approved, etc.

Title: Check learner licence slot availability in Telangana
Description: Users can check the Check learner licence slot availability in the state of Telangana. This online service is provided by the Transport Department of Telangana. You can select District and Test Center to See slot availability.

Title: Pay your commercial tax online for Telangana
Description: Users can pay their commercial taxes online with the help of this portal. This service is provided by the Commercial Department of Telangana Government. You can e-register and make e-payments of commercial taxes through this portal.

Title: Meghalaya Online Education Portal
Description: Meghalaya Online Scholarship Portal is an initiative aimed to facilitate faster and efficient disposal of scholarship applications and timely payment of the scholarships to the students directly in their bank accounts. Users can find live statistics of scholarship applications, live updates of scheme wise applications and other important information pertaining to courses etc. You can also search for applications and login to apply for scholarships.

Title: Apply online to transfer your EPFO claim
Description: Users can apply to transfer their EPFO claims online with the help of this portal. A member has an option to submit his claim either through his present employer or the previous one. You can fill all such claim requests with ease and the employer can verify/correct member's details, approve and submit the requests online through portal.

Title: Register with Swaasth India Portal
Description: Swaasth India will enable physicians of India origin residing globally to support the Government of India's objectives to improve the standard of living and health status of the Indian population in a coordinated way. Swaasth India will provide an online platform to provide information and requirements of government or NGO run health and wellness programs in India to physicians of India origin from around the world, enabling them to enroll and support healthcare needs in villages, districts and states of choice in India.

Title: Book appointment online with Government Hospitals
Description: You can register and get an appointment online for  the government hospitals. Users can get an OPD appointment, lab reports and check blood availability in any government hospital online. Mobile app is also available for users to get an appointment for the government hospitals. The dashboard is given for information about the hospitals registered with the portal, total appointments, government departments, etc.

Title: Apply for jobs on National Career Service Portal
Description: Job seekers can avail the benefits of this portal by registering themselves. You can find career centres, find skill providers and career counsellors, get local help, etc. Employers can also use this portal to find skilled candidates. Information about local employment services, career centres, etc. is available.

Title: Apply for scholarships through National Scholarships Portal
Description: National Scholarships Portal is one-stop solution through which various services starting from student application, application receipt, processing, sanction and disbursal of various scholarships to students are enabled. National Scholarships Portal is taken as Mission Mode Project under National e-Governance Plan (NeGP).

Title: Get Aadhaar Card on Resident Portal
Description: You can now download an electronic version of your Aadhaar Card. E-Aadhaar is as valid as the original Aadhaar letter and can be downloaded on submitting your Aadhaar or the enrolment ID (found on the Enrolment slip given to you at the time of enrolment). Users can get e-Aadhaar, download on their mobile phones and also check the status of their Aadhaar online.

Title: e-Pay your Taxes by Income Tax Department
Description: You can e-Pay your taxes. This online service is provided by the Income Tax Department. e-Payment facilitates payment of direct taxes online by taxpayers. To avail of this facility the taxpayer is required to have a net-banking account with the authorized banks.

Title: Apply online for Permanent Account Number (PAN CARD)
Description: Users can apply online for the Permanent Account Number (PAN CARD) with the help of this online application form provided by the Income Tax Department, Ministry of Finance. PAN Card for an individual, family, firm, local authority, etc. can be applied. You need to fill up this online application form to apply for a Pan Card.

Title: Inform About Missing/Found Children - Khoya-Paya Portal
Description: Khoya-Paya Portal helps parents to register and report online the details of their missing child. Parents, whose child is missing, can register to report a missing kid, give details of missing kid, search missing child details, etc. A dashboard is also available to find information related missing and sighted children.

Title: Check daily Water storages of dams in Maharashtra
Description: Users can check daily water storage of dams in Maharashtra as provided by the Water Resources Department. You can check month and year-wise storage details status in the state. The Consolidated Reservoir Status can also be checked.

Title: Avail online LPG services
Description: You can avail online LPG services with the help of MyLPG Portal. Users can join PAHAL (DBTL) by providing your 17-digit LPG ID. Consumers can also apply to give up their LPG subsidy online. You can provide your 17-digit LPG ID to avail services. Forms for joining the Pahal scheme and getting new LPG connection are also available. Safety tips for LPG consumers are also given.

Title: Apply online for Travel Trade Recognition
Description: The Ministry of Tourism has a scheme of approving Travel Agents, Tour Operators, Adventure Tour Operators and Tourist Transport Operators, the idea being to encourage quality, standard and service in these categories so as to promote Tourism in India. This is a voluntary scheme open to all bonafide agencies. E-Travel Trade Recognition will help all travel agents, inbound tour operators, tourist transport operators, adventure tour operators and domestic tour operators getting their travel trade recognitions online.

Title: Sankalp by Department of Pension & Pensioners' Welfare
Description: Sankalp is an initiative from Department of Pension & Pensioners' Welfare, Government of India, to provide a platform for the pensioners to access opportunities available for useful interventions in the society. It also facilitates the Organizations working in these areas to select appropriate skill and expertise from the available pool of volunteers.

Title: DigiLocker - Register online to store e-documents
Description: DigiLocker can be used to securely store e-documents as well as store Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) link of e-documents issued by various issuer departments. The e-Sign facility provided as part of DigiLocker system can be used to digitally sign e-documents.

Title: Locate nearest Jeevan Pramaan (Digital Life Certificate) Centre
Description: You can find the nearest location of a Jeevan Pramaan Centre online. Users need to specify location type, state, district etc. to locate the nearest Jeevan Pramaan Centre. You can get the exact location of the centre, provided through an interactive map.

Title: Check status of fog affected trains
Description: Check online status of trains affected due to fog. This service is provided by the Indian Railway Catering and Tourism Corporation Limited (IRCTC). You can view train's name, status, expected arrival time, destination, etc.

Title: Apply for Jeevan Pramaan - Digital Life Certificate for Pensioners
Description: Jeevan Pramaan is a biometric enabled digital service for pensioners. Pensioners of Central Government, State Government or any other Government organization can take benefit of this facility. You can register online with the help of this portal and provide your details to get a digital life certificate. Pensioner can find detailed information about this service and locate nearest location of a Jeevan Pramaan Centre. Users can also download mobile apps and avail benefits under this service.

Title: mKisan SMS Portal for farmers
Description: mKisan SMS Portal for farmers enables all Central and State government organizations in agriculture and allied sectors to give information/services/advisories to farmers by SMS in their language, preference of agricultural practices and location. Users can get information on the Push SMS, Pull SMS, services, IVRS, mobile apps, etc. You can also register for SMS services.
